{"title_page": "Montenegrin Water Polo Cup", "text_new": "{{Infobox sports league\n| title          = Montenegrin Water Polo Cup<br>Crnogorski vaterpolo kup\n| current_season = \n| logo           = \n| pixels         = \n| sport          = [[Water polo]]\n| founded        = 2006\n| ceo            = \n| teams          = 8\n| country        = {{flagicon|MNE}} [[Montenegro]]\n| continent      = [[LEN]] ([[Europe]])\n| folded         = \n| champion       = [[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]\n| most_champs    = [[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]<br />\n (11 titles in independent Montenegro; 14 overall)\n| sponsor        = \n| TV             = [[Radio Television of Montenegro|RTCG]]\n| website        = [http://wpolo.me/ wpolo.me]\n}}\n'''Montenegrin Water Polo Cup''' ([[Montenegrin language|Montenegrin]]: Crnogorski vaterpolski kup) is a national [[water polo]] cup played in [[Montenegro]]. It is organized by the [[Water Polo and Swimming Federation of Montenegro]].\n\n==History==\n===Montenegrin clubs in Yugoslav Cup===\nBefore [[Montenegrin independence referendum, 2006|Montenegrin independence]], clubs from that Republic played in national water polo Yugoslav Cup and Cup of Serbia and Montenegro]]. Most successful was [[PVK Jadran]] with three trophies won. [[VK Primorac Kotor|VK Primorac]] won two Yugoslav cups.<br />\nBelow is a list of Yugoslav Cup trophies won by Montenegrin clubs.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\n|-\n! Club\n! Winners\n! Runners-up\n! Winning Years\n|-\n| [[PVK Jadran|Jadran Herceg Novi]]\n| <center>3</center>\n| <center>4</center>\n| 2003-04, 2004-05, 2005-06\n|-\n| [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac Kotor]]\n| <center>2</center>\n| <center>2</center>\n|1985-86, 2002-03\n|-\n| [[VK Budva|Budva]]\n| <center>-</center>\n| <center>4</center>\n|\n|}\n\n===Montenegrin Cup (2006-)===\nExcept [[Montenegrin First League of Water Polo]] as a top-tier league competition, after the independence, Water polo Federation of Montenegro established Montenegrin Cup as a second elite national tournament. Inaugural season of Montenegrin Cup was 2006-07, and by now most successful was PVK Jadran with 11 titles (14 including Yugoslav Cup trophies). Except them, trophy of Montenegrin Cup, during the history, won VK Primorac and [[VK Budva]].<br />\nFrom season 2016-17, there is a final-four tournament in Montenegrin Cup. Since then, three times the host of final four tournament was [[Nik\u0161i\u0107]] and once [[Podgorica]].\n\n==Winners and finals==\n\n===Season by season===\nBelow is a list of final matches of Montenegrin Cup since the season 2006-07.\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Winner !! Runner-up !! Final result\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2006\u201307 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|7:6, 11:7\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2007\u201308 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|7:9, 9:6\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2008\u201309 || '''[[VK Budva|Budva]]''' || [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]] || align=\"center\"|League system\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2009\u201310 || '''[[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|8:7\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2010\u201311 || '''[[VK Budva|Budva]]''' || [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]] || align=\"center\"|10:8, 8:9\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2011\u201312 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|11:12, 12:10\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2012\u201313 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]] || align=\"center\"|6:7, 10:8\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2013\u201314 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]] || align=\"center\"|12:10, 4:6 (4:1)\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2014\u201315 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|7:5, 7:5\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2015\u201316 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|17:5, 10:5\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2016\u201317 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]] || align=\"center\"|9:9 (5:3)\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2017\u201318 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|12:8\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2018\u201319 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|12:8\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2019\u201320 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|9:8\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Titles by Club ===\n==== Montenegrin League ====\nBelow is a list of clubs with titles won in Montenegrin Water Polo Cup.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\n|-\n! Club !! Titles !! Runners-up !! Years Won\n|-\n| [[PVK Jadran|Jadran Herceg Novi]] || align=\"center\"|11 || align=\"center\"|- || 2006\u201307, 2007\u201308, 2011\u201312, 2012\u201313, 2013\u201314, 2014\u201315, 2015\u201316, 2016\u201317, 2017\u201318, 2018\u201319, 2019\u201320\n|-\n| [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|2 || align=\"center\"|9 || 2008\u201309, 2010\u201311\n|-\n| [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac Kotor]] || align=\"center\"|1 || align=\"center\"|5 || 2009-10\n|}\n\n==== Overall ====\nBelow is an overall list, with titles won in Montenegrin Cup and SFR Yugoslavia / Serbia and Montenegro Cup.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\n|-\n! Club !! Titles !! Runners-up !! Years Won\n|-\n| [[PVK Jadran|Jadran Herceg Novi]] || align=\"center\"|14 || align=\"center\"|4 || 2003\u201304, 2004\u201305, 2005\u201306, 2006\u201307, 2007\u201308, 2011\u201312, 2012\u201313, 2013\u201314, 2014\u201315, 2015\u201316, 2016\u201317, 2017\u201318, 2018\u201319, 2019\u201320\n|-\n| [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac Kotor]] || align=\"center\"|3 || align=\"center\"|7 || 1985\u201386, 2002\u201303, 2009\u201310\n|-\n| [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|2 || align=\"center\"|13 || 2008\u201309, 2010\u201311\n|}\nSource:<ref>http://www.pvkjadran.com/index.php/2014-10-27-15-25-28/istorijat</ref><ref>http://www.vkbudva.com/index.php/o-klubu</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Montenegrin First League of Water Polo]]\n* [[Montenegrin Second League of Water Polo]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://wpolo.me Water Polo and Swimming Federation of Montenegro]\n\n{{Sport in Montenegro}}\n\n[[Category:Water polo competitions in Montenegro|Cup]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox sports league\n| title          = Montenegrin Water Polo Cup<br>Crnogorski vaterpolo kup\n| current_season = \n| logo           = \n| pixels         = \n| sport          = [[Water polo]]\n| founded        = 2006\n| ceo            = \n| teams          = 8\n| country        = {{flagicon|MNE}} [[Montenegro]]\n| continent      = [[LEN]] ([[Europe]])\n| folded         = \n| champion       = [[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]\n| most_champs    = [[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]<br />\n (11 titles in independent Montenegro; 14 overall)\n| sponsor        = \n| TV             = [[Radio Television of Montenegro|RTCG]]\n| website        = [http://wpolo.me/ wpolo.me]\n}}\n'''Montenegrin Water Polo Cup''' ([[Montenegrin language|Montenegrin]]: Crnogorski vaterpolski kup) is a national [[water polo]] cup played in [[Montenegro]]. It is organized by the [[Water Polo and Swimming Federation of Montenegro]].\n\n==History==\n===Montenegrin clubs in Yugoslav Cup===\nBefore [[Montenegrin independence referendum, 2006|Montenegrin independence]], clubs from that Republic played in national water polo Yugoslav Cup and Cup of Serbia and Montenegro]]. Most successful was [[PVK Jadran]] with three trophies won. [[VK Primorac Kotor|VK Primorac]] won two Yugoslav cups.<br />\nBelow is a list of Yugoslav Cup trophies won by Montenegrin clubs.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\n|-\n! Club\n! Winners\n! Runners-up\n! Winning Years\n|-\n| [[PVK Jadran|Jadran Herceg Novi]]\n| <center>3</center>\n| <center>4</center>\n| 2003-04, 2004-05, 2005-06\n|-\n| [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac Kotor]]\n| <center>2</center>\n| <center>2</center>\n|1985-86, 2002-03\n|-\n| [[VK Budva|Budva]]\n| <center>-</center>\n| <center>4</center>\n|\n|}\n\n===Montenegrin Cup (2006-)===\nExcept [[Montenegrin First League of Water Polo]] as a top-tier league competition, after the independence, Water polo Federation of Montenegro established Montenegrin Cup as a second elite national tournament. Inaugural season of Montenegrin Cup was 2006-07, and by now most successful was PVK Jadran with 11 titles (14 including Yugoslav Cup trophies). Except them, trophy of Montenegrin Cup, during the history, won VK Primorac and [[VK Budva]].<br />\nFrom season 2016-17, there is a final-four tournament in Montenegrin Cup. Since then, three times the host of final four tournament was [[Nik\u0161i\u0107]] and once [[Podgorica]].\n\n==Winners and finals==\n\n===Season by season===\nBelow is a list of final matches of Montenegrin Cup since the season 2006-07.\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Winner !! Runner-up !! Final result\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2006\u201307 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|7:6, 11:7\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2007\u201308 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|7:9, 9:6\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2008\u201309 || '''[[VK Budva|Budva]]''' || [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]] || align=\"center\"|League system\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2009\u201310 || '''[[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|8:7\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2010\u201311 || '''[[VK Budva|Budva]]''' || [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]] || align=\"center\"|10:8, 8:9\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2011\u201312 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|11:12, 12:10\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2012\u201313 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]] || align=\"center\"|6:7, 10:8\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2013\u201314 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Primorac Kotor|Primorac]] || align=\"center\"|12:10, 4:6 (4:1)\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|2014\u201315 || '''[[PVK Jadran|Jadran]]''' || [[VK Budva|Budva]] || align=\"center\"|7:5, 7:5\n|-\n|al